00:00:08.776 --> 00:00:09.911 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:00:10.043 --> 00:00:11.278 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:00:12.847 --> 00:00:15.315 position:38% line:89% align:start
[heaves]

00:00:17.184 --> 00:00:18.418 position:44% line:89% align:start
Um...

00:00:18.553 --> 00:00:20.420 position:19% line:83% align:start
Excuse me, could I ask
what your name is?

00:00:20.555 --> 00:00:22.724 position:13% line:89% align:start
Uh, it's Hiroto Shinohara.

00:00:23.123 --> 00:00:24.726 position:27% line:89% align:start
Master Shinohara?

00:00:27.562 --> 00:00:29.429 position:27% line:83% align:start
I beg your pardon
for my lapse in decorum,

00:00:29.564 --> 00:00:32.032 position:21% line:83% align:start
I imagine I appeared
quite foolish hiding as I did.

00:00:32.165 --> 00:00:33.233 position:24% line:89% align:start
Please, forgive me.

00:00:33.367 --> 00:00:34.936 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
Silky white hair!

00:00:35.068 --> 00:00:38.405 position:7% line:83% align:start
Small face! Big eyes! Oh, man!
Even her voice is adorable!

00:00:38.540 --> 00:00:41.208 position:10% line:83% align:start
Um, why exactly did you hide,
Miss?

00:00:41.341 --> 00:00:43.243 position:16% line:89% align:start
No need to be so formal.

00:00:43.377 --> 00:00:44.746 position:35% line:83% align:start
It's simply
that I wasn't informed

00:00:44.879 --> 00:00:46.915 position:24% line:83% align:start
you would be male,
Master Shinohara.

00:00:47.549 --> 00:00:49.784 position:35% line:83% align:start
But still,
the fact is immaterial

00:00:49.918 --> 00:00:51.151 position:19% line:89% align:start
to my responsibilities.

00:00:51.285 --> 00:00:52.754 position:21% line:89% align:start
I'm Shirayuki Himeji,

00:00:52.887 --> 00:00:55.523 position:21% line:83% align:start
a student enrolled in
District Three's Ouka Academy

00:00:55.657 --> 00:00:58.492 position:10% line:83% align:start
on request of District Four's
Headmistress Ichinose.

00:00:58.626 --> 00:01:00.193 position:27% line:83% align:start
I will be serving
in the capacity

00:01:00.327 --> 00:01:02.730 position:13% line:83% align:start
of your live-in assistant,
starting from today.

00:01:03.330 --> 00:01:04.732 position:35% line:89% align:start
Come again?

00:01:05.667 --> 00:01:08.836 position:50% line:89% align:start
âª

00:02:35.556 --> 00:02:36.758 position:35% line:83% align:start
[SHIRAYUKI]
Some tea.

00:02:36.891 --> 00:02:38.559 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
What did you mean by "live-in"?

00:02:38.693 --> 00:02:40.028 position:10% line:89% align:start
I don't believe it to be far

00:02:40.160 --> 00:02:41.562 position:44% line:83% align:start
from
the conventional definition.

00:02:41.696 --> 00:02:43.230 position:13% line:89% align:start
I will live and sleep here,

00:02:43.363 --> 00:02:46.000 position:10% line:83% align:start
aiding you in whatever manner
I'm able, sir.

00:02:46.134 --> 00:02:47.502 position:35% line:89% align:start
Sleep here?

00:02:47.635 --> 00:02:49.504 position:19% line:83% align:start
I apologize in advance
for any disappointment,

00:02:49.637 --> 00:02:51.639 position:27% line:83% align:start
but we will have
separate bedrooms.

00:02:51.773 --> 00:02:54.742 position:13% line:83% align:start
Disappointment? That's not
really the issue here.

00:02:55.009 --> 00:02:57.779 position:44% line:83% align:start
-Huh?
-Never mind, forget about it.

00:02:57.912 --> 00:02:59.647 position:24% line:83% align:start
I just didn't think
that you'd like.

00:02:59.781 --> 00:03:03.084 position:13% line:83% align:start
-I don't, not in the least.
-You're giving me mixed signals!

00:03:03.216 --> 00:03:04.686 position:5% line:89% align:start
My reservations aren't personal,

00:03:04.819 --> 00:03:06.954 position:19% line:83% align:start
I'm merely unaccustomed
to the male presence.

00:03:07.088 --> 00:03:10.223 position:24% line:83% align:start
My ire is entirely
for Headmistress Ichinose.

00:03:11.125 --> 00:03:13.360 position:13% line:83% align:start
Huh, I don't know what beef
you have with her,

00:03:13.493 --> 00:03:15.563 position:13% line:89% align:start
but trust me, I can relate.

00:03:15.697 --> 00:03:17.364 position:35% line:83% align:start
[SHIRAYUKI]
Then we have common ground,

00:03:17.497 --> 00:03:19.266 position:21% line:83% align:start
as good a sign as any
for the prospect

00:03:19.399 --> 00:03:20.902 position:16% line:83% align:start
of peaceful coexistence,
say Master?

00:03:21.035 --> 00:03:22.670 position:24% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO] You know,
you can sit down if you want.

00:03:22.804 --> 00:03:25.039 position:21% line:83% align:start
[SHIRAYUKI] I'm fine.
Please don't worry about me.

00:03:25.173 --> 00:03:27.642 position:24% line:83% align:start
A maid does not sit
in the presence of her betters.

00:03:27.775 --> 00:03:29.409 position:7% line:83% align:start
Look, you're making me nervous,
you know?

00:03:29.544 --> 00:03:31.546 position:10% line:83% align:start
We're both here at the whims
of the Headmistress.

00:03:31.679 --> 00:03:33.748 position:5% line:89% align:start
No need to put me on a pedestal.

00:03:34.281 --> 00:03:36.684 position:35% line:83% align:start
[SHIRAYUKI]
Uh, well. If you insist.

00:03:36.818 --> 00:03:39.252 position:10% line:83% align:start
I would hate for you to feel
uncomfortable, Master.

00:03:39.386 --> 00:03:41.155 position:24% line:83% align:start
You called yourself
an "assistant",

00:03:41.288 --> 00:03:43.658 position:7% line:83% align:start
so I'm guessing you're not just
a regular housemaid.

00:03:43.791 --> 00:03:48.395 position:13% line:83% align:start
Observant. Tell me, Master,
when was it you last ate?

00:03:49.362 --> 00:03:50.497 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
Huh?

00:03:51.933 --> 00:03:52.900 position:41% line:89% align:start
Dig in.

00:03:53.034 --> 00:03:55.402 position:13% line:89% align:start
No way! Is this all for me?

00:03:55.536 --> 00:03:58.072 position:24% line:83% align:start
Yes, perhaps I made
a little more than necessary.

00:03:58.206 --> 00:04:00.675 position:30% line:83% align:start
"A little more"
is kind of underselling it.

00:04:00.808 --> 00:04:02.677 position:13% line:83% align:start
You're gonna have some too,
right?

00:04:02.810 --> 00:04:04.078 position:35% line:83% align:start
[SHIRAYUKI]
I'll wait until after

00:04:04.212 --> 00:04:05.445 position:16% line:89% align:start
you're finished, Master.

00:04:05.580 --> 00:04:07.014 position:41% line:83% align:start
No, no!
It'll have gone cold by then,

00:04:07.148 --> 00:04:08.516 position:13% line:89% align:start
you can help me eat it now.

00:04:08.649 --> 00:04:11.318 position:35% line:83% align:start
Very well,
if you wish for me to do so.

00:04:11.451 --> 00:04:13.121 position:13% line:89% align:start
Right, I guess I'll dig in.

00:04:13.253 --> 00:04:14.689 position:35% line:89% align:start
[chomping]

00:04:14.822 --> 00:04:17.925 position:24% line:83% align:start
This is delicious!
Such succulent, divine flavors.

00:04:18.059 --> 00:04:19.259 position:19% line:89% align:start
Could this perfect meal

00:04:19.392 --> 00:04:20.928 position:21% line:83% align:start
truly have been made
by human hands?

00:04:21.062 --> 00:04:22.262 position:21% line:89% align:start
I'm not entirely sure

00:04:22.395 --> 00:04:23.731 position:16% line:83% align:start
whether that's flattering
or belittling.

00:04:23.865 --> 00:04:25.465 position:35% line:83% align:start
Words fail,
and praise is not enough,

00:04:25.600 --> 00:04:26.968 position:24% line:89% align:start
this is everything!

00:04:27.267 --> 00:04:28.636 position:24% line:89% align:start
My, how unexpected.

00:04:28.770 --> 00:04:30.370 position:13% line:83% align:start
You certainly are effusive
with your feelings,

00:04:30.505 --> 00:04:31.572 position:27% line:89% align:start
Master Shinohara.

00:04:31.706 --> 00:04:33.975 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
Huh? Yeah, I guess I am.

00:04:34.108 --> 00:04:36.110 position:24% line:83% align:start
I'd actually heard
that you were exceedingly adept

00:04:36.244 --> 00:04:37.612 position:16% line:89% align:start
at hiding what you felt.

00:04:37.745 --> 00:04:40.581 position:16% line:83% align:start
Hm, yeah, but I can swing
to the other extreme

00:04:40.715 --> 00:04:41.916 position:16% line:89% align:start
when I let my guard down.

00:04:42.049 --> 00:04:43.316 position:35% line:89% align:start
[chomping]

00:04:43.450 --> 00:04:44.952 position:35% line:83% align:start
[SHIRAYUKI]
And your guard is down now?

00:04:45.086 --> 00:04:46.587 position:19% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO] Yeah. I mean,
it's not like you've given me

00:04:46.721 --> 00:04:48.556 position:16% line:83% align:start
any reason to be on edge
or anything.

00:04:48.689 --> 00:04:53.594 position:10% line:83% align:start
Oh. I see. Any food aversions
I should know about?

00:04:53.728 --> 00:04:55.395 position:33% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO] Nah,
I'll eat just about anything!

00:04:55.530 --> 00:04:57.297 position:10% line:89% align:start
Especially if it's this good.

00:04:57.430 --> 00:04:59.600 position:35% line:89% align:start
[chuckles]

00:05:03.070 --> 00:05:06.107 position:21% line:83% align:start
Alright, we'll start
with a detailed overview.

00:05:06.240 --> 00:05:07.909 position:5% line:89% align:start
To prevent unauthorized access,

00:05:08.042 --> 00:05:10.410 position:24% line:83% align:start
I'll be displaying
this content offline.

00:05:10.545 --> 00:05:12.213 position:10% line:89% align:start
If anyone were to spy on us,

00:05:12.345 --> 00:05:14.215 position:21% line:83% align:start
it would spell an end
to all this.

00:05:14.347 --> 00:05:15.783 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
She's not wrong.

00:05:15.917 --> 00:05:17.919 position:21% line:83% align:start
By using the Red Star
to become a fake Seven Star,

00:05:18.052 --> 00:05:20.453 position:13% line:83% align:start
we're basically pulling off
one huge scam.

00:05:20.588 --> 00:05:23.291 position:16% line:83% align:start
This isn't morally gray,
it's black as sin

00:05:23.423 --> 00:05:24.992 position:24% line:83% align:start
and if it gets out,
I'm done for.

00:05:25.126 --> 00:05:29.297 position:7% line:83% align:start
Academy Island. Save for Zero,
each district has one.

00:05:29.429 --> 00:05:31.732 position:38% line:83% align:start
Resulting
in a grand total of twenty.

00:05:31.866 --> 00:05:35.303 position:13% line:83% align:start
These academies are ranked
and scored on a yearly basis.

00:05:35.703 --> 00:05:37.437 position:33% line:83% align:start
In accordance
with their rank placement

00:05:37.572 --> 00:05:40.208 position:19% line:83% align:start
each academy is granted
certain privileges.

00:05:40.340 --> 00:05:42.543 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
Uh, do the students' Stars

00:05:42.677 --> 00:05:43.878 position:10% line:89% align:start
have anything to do with it?

00:05:44.011 --> 00:05:45.445 position:35% line:83% align:start
[SHIRAYUKI]
Indeed they do.

00:05:45.580 --> 00:05:47.380 position:24% line:83% align:start
Students possessing
five or more Stars

00:05:47.515 --> 00:05:48.783 position:7% line:89% align:start
are considered to be advanced.

00:05:48.916 --> 00:05:50.585 position:27% line:83% align:start
The more of those
an academy has,

00:05:50.718 --> 00:05:52.153 position:5% line:89% align:start
the higher its ranking will be,

00:05:52.286 --> 00:05:54.222 position:10% line:83% align:start
and should one have a student
with Seven Stars?

00:05:54.354 --> 00:05:55.422 position:19% line:89% align:start
It'll usually rank top.

00:05:55.556 --> 00:05:56.791 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
Well, that explains

00:05:56.924 --> 00:05:59.126 position:21% line:83% align:start
why the headmistress
was so on-to-con.

00:05:59.260 --> 00:06:00.995 position:7% line:83% align:start
[SHIRAYUKI] And this tremendous
systemic value

00:06:01.128 --> 00:06:04.165 position:13% line:83% align:start
is also why the Seven Stars
are so thoroughly targeted.

00:06:04.298 --> 00:06:05.833 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
That makes sense.

00:06:05.967 --> 00:06:09.103 position:5% line:83% align:start
If a Six Star beats me, they can
take my position at the top.

00:06:09.237 --> 00:06:10.771 position:35% line:89% align:start
But still,

00:06:10.905 --> 00:06:12.372 position:7% line:83% align:start
they're putting their own Stars
on-the-line too, right?

00:06:12.506 --> 00:06:13.875 position:35% line:83% align:start
[SHIRAYUKI]
Yes. However,

00:06:14.008 --> 00:06:15.943 position:10% line:83% align:start
the reward outweighs the risk
for lower ranks.

00:06:16.077 --> 00:06:17.712 position:19% line:83% align:start
So, even a small chance
of winning

00:06:17.845 --> 00:06:19.580 position:19% line:83% align:start
is statistically worth
the gamble.

00:06:19.714 --> 00:06:21.849 position:24% line:83% align:start
Also, the abilities
of a Seven Star typically help

00:06:21.983 --> 00:06:24.619 position:13% line:83% align:start
mitigate the threats posed
to them. Case in point.

00:06:24.752 --> 00:06:27.054 position:13% line:83% align:start
These are the game results
over the past year

00:06:27.188 --> 00:06:28.789 position:16% line:89% align:start
for The Empress, Saionji.

00:06:28.923 --> 00:06:32.226 position:10% line:83% align:start
Sadly, her defensive arsenal
isn't available to you, Master.

00:06:32.360 --> 00:06:33.594 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
Huh? Why not?

00:06:33.728 --> 00:06:35.029 position:35% line:83% align:start
[SHIRAYUKI]
Because of your score

00:06:35.162 --> 00:06:36.197 position:21% line:89% align:start
on the transfer exam.

00:06:36.330 --> 00:06:37.698 position:38% line:89% align:start
[groans]

00:06:37.832 --> 00:06:39.000 position:24% line:83% align:start
[SHIRAYUKI] A score
so outstandingly pathetic,

00:06:39.133 --> 00:06:40.935 position:19% line:83% align:start
it's almost unbearable
to look at.

00:06:41.068 --> 00:06:42.937 position:24% line:83% align:start
I fear most schools
would have laughed you out.

00:06:43.070 --> 00:06:44.171 position:38% line:89% align:start
[groans]

00:06:44.305 --> 00:06:45.806 position:35% line:83% align:start
[SHIRAYUKI]
Pardon my candor.

00:06:45.940 --> 00:06:48.576 position:13% line:83% align:start
At any rate, your true rank
is still One Star, Master.

00:06:48.709 --> 00:06:50.278 position:5% line:89% align:start
Meaning that, in upcoming games,

00:06:50.410 --> 00:06:53.648 position:10% line:83% align:start
you will only be able to use
abilities at a One Star level.

00:06:53.781 --> 00:06:55.549 position:24% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO] Those are
the weakest ones, aren't they?

00:06:55.683 --> 00:06:56.984 position:35% line:83% align:start
[SHIRAYUKI]
Yes.

00:06:57.118 --> 00:06:58.219 position:7% line:83% align:start
You'll essentially be fighting
boss battles

00:06:58.352 --> 00:06:59.887 position:19% line:89% align:start
as a level one player.

00:07:00.021 --> 00:07:01.956 position:16% line:83% align:start
That doesn't sound good,
but I'm guessing

00:07:02.089 --> 00:07:04.325 position:16% line:83% align:start
that's kind of the reason
you were sent here, wasn't it?

00:07:04.457 --> 00:07:07.094 position:10% line:83% align:start
[SHIRAYUKI] That is correct.
Now listen carefully.

00:07:07.228 --> 00:07:09.330 position:19% line:83% align:start
For the next two years,
we in the Company will do

00:07:09.462 --> 00:07:12.199 position:13% line:83% align:start
everything we possibly can
to assist you, Master.

00:07:12.333 --> 00:07:15.569 position:19% line:83% align:start
Not only in your games,
but also in your daily life.

00:07:15.703 --> 00:07:17.470 position:5% line:83% align:start
As long as you're able to uphold
the act,

00:07:17.605 --> 00:07:19.340 position:19% line:83% align:start
and maintain your rank
as Seven Star.

00:07:19.472 --> 00:07:23.144 position:16% line:83% align:start
Then we will be complicit
in your lie, Master Shinohara.

00:07:23.277 --> 00:07:24.879 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
Sweet salvation!

00:07:25.012 --> 00:07:27.848 position:7% line:83% align:start
Oh! Games are all one-one-ones,
though, aren't they?

00:07:27.982 --> 00:07:30.483 position:21% line:83% align:start
If someone helps me,
it'll be obvious.

00:07:33.154 --> 00:07:35.323 position:19% line:83% align:start
[SHIRAYUKI] Do you see
the game icon in the center?

00:07:35.455 --> 00:07:36.724 position:19% line:89% align:start
You've likely received

00:07:36.857 --> 00:07:38.426 position:21% line:83% align:start
a substantial number
of game requests by now.

00:07:38.559 --> 00:07:40.828 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
What? Forty-two already?

00:07:40.962 --> 00:07:43.496 position:13% line:83% align:start
-Scroll down a bit, please.
-Huh?

00:07:43.631 --> 00:07:45.132 position:13% line:89% align:start
Right, you can stop there.

00:07:45.266 --> 00:07:47.401 position:21% line:83% align:start
We'll choose that one
for your first match,

00:07:47.535 --> 00:07:49.236 position:13% line:89% align:start
scheduled tomorrow morning.

00:07:49.770 --> 00:07:51.639 position:19% line:89% align:start
Uh, that's really soon.

00:07:51.772 --> 00:07:53.307 position:13% line:89% align:start
Which will make an impact.

00:07:53.441 --> 00:07:55.743 position:7% line:83% align:start
You received a lot of attention
for beating the Empress

00:07:55.876 --> 00:07:57.945 position:10% line:83% align:start
on your first day of school,
Master.

00:07:58.713 --> 00:08:00.247 position:33% line:83% align:start
[SHIRAKYUKI]
But at this stage,

00:08:00.381 --> 00:08:02.083 position:16% line:83% align:start
there will still be those
second-guessing your strength.

00:08:02.216 --> 00:08:05.853 position:41% line:83% align:start
And so,
a further example must be made.

00:08:05.987 --> 00:08:08.589 position:7% line:83% align:start
In addition to that, we can use
this game to demonstrate

00:08:08.723 --> 00:08:10.324 position:10% line:89% align:start
how our assistance will work.

00:08:10.458 --> 00:08:13.995 position:7% line:83% align:start
And you're sure I'm gonna win?
I'm just a One Star, remember?

00:08:14.128 --> 00:08:14.929 position:41% line:89% align:start
So how?

00:08:15.396 --> 00:08:17.598 position:35% line:83% align:start
[SHIRAYUKI]
That should be obvious by now.

00:08:17.732 --> 00:08:20.101 position:10% line:89% align:start
If you wanna win, you cheat.

00:08:20.935 --> 00:08:23.104 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
What do you mean by "cheat?"

00:08:23.771 --> 00:08:24.872 position:24% line:89% align:start
Hacking, of course.

00:08:25.406 --> 00:08:27.041 position:33% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO] And
how're we supposed to do that?

00:08:27.508 --> 00:08:29.810 position:16% line:83% align:start
[SHIRAYUKI] Could you put
this earbud in, please?

00:08:29.944 --> 00:08:31.445 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
Uh, right now?

00:08:31.579 --> 00:08:34.615 position:16% line:83% align:start
[SHIRAYUKI] The Company's
Head of Electronics, Kagaya.

00:08:34.749 --> 00:08:36.951 position:38% line:83% align:start
[KAGAYA]
Hey, bro! How's it going?

00:08:37.084 --> 00:08:39.453 position:35% line:83% align:start
I'm Kagaya,
the 'big sis' around here.

00:08:39.587 --> 00:08:40.755 position:27% line:89% align:start
Nice to meet you.

00:08:40.888 --> 00:08:42.523 position:19% line:89% align:start
Uh, sure, good evening.

00:08:42.656 --> 00:08:43.958 position:38% line:83% align:start
[KAGAYA]
Nah, that's way too stiff!

00:08:44.091 --> 00:08:46.861 position:5% line:83% align:start
Let's try something more snappy,
like, Hiro?

00:08:46.994 --> 00:08:48.696 position:38% line:83% align:start
-[sighs]
-[KAGAYA] Alright!

00:08:48.829 --> 00:08:50.131 position:24% line:89% align:start
He's cool with it!

00:08:50.264 --> 00:08:51.966 position:21% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO] This girl's
in a world of her own.

00:08:52.099 --> 00:08:53.267 position:27% line:89% align:start
As you can tell,

00:08:53.401 --> 00:08:54.869 position:16% line:83% align:start
Kagaya's social etiquette
is somewhat lacking,

00:08:55.002 --> 00:08:56.871 position:30% line:83% align:start
but her skills
more than make up for it.

00:08:57.438 --> 00:08:59.540 position:24% line:83% align:start
[SHIRAYUKI] Kagaya
will be able to hack her way

00:08:59.673 --> 00:09:01.008 position:10% line:89% align:start
into your opponent's Device.

00:09:01.142 --> 00:09:03.377 position:30% line:83% align:start
Manipulating it
to our advantage.

00:09:03.844 --> 00:09:05.179 position:19% line:89% align:start
So, it's quite simple.

00:09:05.312 --> 00:09:06.914 position:13% line:83% align:start
If you don't draw attention
to the hacking,

00:09:07.048 --> 00:09:09.984 position:16% line:83% align:start
victory is just a matter
of keeping up appearances.

00:09:10.519 --> 00:09:12.119 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
Just like that?

00:09:12.253 --> 00:09:13.821 position:30% line:83% align:start
I mean, I know
I'm not directly involved

00:09:13.954 --> 00:09:15.423 position:10% line:89% align:start
but isn't this sort of wrong?

00:09:15.990 --> 00:09:17.224 position:35% line:83% align:start
[SHIRAYUKI]
Well, of course it's wrong.

00:09:17.358 --> 00:09:19.126 position:33% line:83% align:start
Third parties
interfering with a game

00:09:19.260 --> 00:09:20.294 position:21% line:89% align:start
is against the rules.

00:09:20.428 --> 00:09:22.596 position:30% line:83% align:start
So is accessing
someone else's Device.

00:09:22.730 --> 00:09:24.065 position:10% line:89% align:start
It's an instant-ban offense,

00:09:24.198 --> 00:09:26.434 position:38% line:83% align:start
in fact,
but that works to our favor.

00:09:26.901 --> 00:09:29.336 position:19% line:83% align:start
The Company would never
botch a task this delicate.

00:09:29.470 --> 00:09:31.639 position:13% line:89% align:start
Amazing, if not terrifying.

00:09:32.473 --> 00:09:34.909 position:10% line:83% align:start
[ICHINOSE] But do you really
want it to end like that?

00:09:35.042 --> 00:09:38.579 position:16% line:83% align:start
Didn't you have a reason
for coming here? A goal?

00:09:39.447 --> 00:09:41.315 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
That's right. I do.

00:09:42.249 --> 00:09:43.150 position:38% line:89% align:start
[grunts]

00:09:43.717 --> 00:09:45.554 position:27% line:83% align:start
I'll do whatever
it takes to win!

00:09:45.686 --> 00:09:47.788 position:16% line:89% align:start
I will be the strongest.

00:09:48.589 --> 00:09:50.091 position:41% line:89% align:start
[ding]

00:09:51.392 --> 00:09:52.726 position:38% line:83% align:start
[KAGAYA]
Way to go, Hiro!

00:09:52.860 --> 00:09:54.361 position:35% line:83% align:start
-[giggles]
-[chuckles]

00:09:54.495 --> 00:09:56.330 position:19% line:83% align:start
[KAGAYA] When I hack in
and seize control of the game

00:09:56.464 --> 00:09:58.999 position:33% line:83% align:start
your victory
is pretty much inevitable.

00:10:00.101 --> 00:10:01.268 position:38% line:89% align:start
[grunts]

00:10:01.402 --> 00:10:05.072 position:30% line:89% align:start
I-I won. I won!

00:10:05.206 --> 00:10:06.607 position:35% line:83% align:start
[SHIRAYUKI]
Was that alright, Mast--

00:10:06.740 --> 00:10:08.476 position:38% line:83% align:start
Alright?
That was unbelievable!

00:10:08.609 --> 00:10:12.346 position:19% line:83% align:start
You said it'd be easy,
but, man, that was effortless.

00:10:12.480 --> 00:10:14.281 position:13% line:89% align:start
Seriously, you're the best!

00:10:14.415 --> 00:10:16.050 position:35% line:83% align:start
[SHIRAYUKI]
Then you acknowledge our skills?

00:10:16.183 --> 00:10:18.052 position:5% line:89% align:start
I sure do! I've got total faith!

00:10:18.185 --> 00:10:19.887 position:33% line:83% align:start
From here on,
I'm counting on you!

00:10:20.020 --> 00:10:21.556 position:13% line:89% align:start
Let's make this thing work!

00:10:21.689 --> 00:10:23.224 position:35% line:83% align:start
[SHIRAYUKI]
Understood.

00:10:23.357 --> 00:10:25.759 position:5% line:83% align:start
And if you don't mind me saying,
your performance was exquisite.

00:10:25.893 --> 00:10:27.194 position:24% line:89% align:start
Well done, Master.

00:10:27.328 --> 00:10:29.564 position:21% line:83% align:start
Now, it's about time
you headed to campus.

00:10:29.697 --> 00:10:30.931 position:41% line:89% align:start
Right.

00:10:32.266 --> 00:10:34.268 position:27% line:83% align:start
[TATARA] You mind
if I call you Shinohara?

00:10:34.401 --> 00:10:35.604 position:27% line:89% align:start
I'm Fuuka Tatara.

00:10:35.736 --> 00:10:37.037 position:19% line:89% align:start
2-A's class president.

00:10:37.506 --> 00:10:39.807 position:13% line:83% align:start
I can answer any questions
you have, Shinohara.

00:10:39.940 --> 00:10:41.976 position:19% line:83% align:start
Like what's best to eat
in the cafeteria.

00:10:42.109 --> 00:10:44.979 position:10% line:83% align:start
I don't think that'll be high
on the priority list, Tatara.

00:10:45.112 --> 00:10:46.747 position:16% line:89% align:start
What? Why wouldn't it be?

00:10:46.881 --> 00:10:49.083 position:13% line:89% align:start
I'm Yuuki Tsuji. Pleasure.

00:10:49.216 --> 00:10:50.151 position:44% line:89% align:start
Yeah.

00:10:50.784 --> 00:10:52.086 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
I was a little surprised

00:10:52.219 --> 00:10:53.687 position:30% line:83% align:start
when I learned
the class had a tournament

00:10:53.821 --> 00:10:55.422 position:30% line:83% align:start
just to decide
who'd get to show me around.

00:10:56.457 --> 00:10:58.425 position:33% line:83% align:start
So, are games
actually pushed here

00:10:58.560 --> 00:10:59.994 position:5% line:89% align:start
