00:12:20.575 --> 00:12:22.711 position:19% line:83% align:start
The ruthlessly cunning,
fearlessly outrageous,

00:12:22.843 --> 00:12:26.046 position:27% line:83% align:start
proudly arrogant,
Hiroto Shinohara!

00:12:26.814 --> 00:12:29.350 position:10% line:83% align:start
So how you feline, Shinohara?
Pumped up and ready?

00:12:29.483 --> 00:12:32.186 position:35% line:83% align:start
Pumped up?
I don't see why I should be.

00:12:32.520 --> 00:12:34.589 position:27% line:83% align:start
My victory is all
but inevitable.

00:12:34.723 --> 00:12:35.856 position:35% line:89% align:start
[chuckles]

00:12:35.990 --> 00:12:37.592 position:27% line:83% align:start
He's cool, calm,
and confident, isn't he?

00:12:37.726 --> 00:12:39.126 position:38% line:89% align:start
[screams]

00:12:39.260 --> 00:12:40.662 position:24% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO] That line
is so coming back to haunt me!

00:12:40.794 --> 00:12:43.598 position:16% line:83% align:start
Why do I keep coming off
like an egotistical monster?

00:12:43.732 --> 00:12:44.865 position:38% line:83% align:start
[SUZURAN]
And meow,

00:12:44.999 --> 00:12:46.668 position:30% line:83% align:start
please welcome
our special guest!

00:12:47.535 --> 00:12:49.436 position:24% line:83% align:start
[SARASA] Thank you!
It's a pleasure to be here!

00:12:49.571 --> 00:12:51.071 position:24% line:89% align:start
I'm Sarasa Saionji.

00:12:51.740 --> 00:12:53.274 position:38% line:89% align:start
[giggles]

00:12:53.407 --> 00:12:55.909 position:5% line:83% align:start
That certainly was some amusing,
if not indulgent preamble, huh?

00:12:56.043 --> 00:12:57.211 position:10% line:89% align:start
Now who else is ready to see

00:12:57.344 --> 00:12:59.280 position:30% line:83% align:start
what these two
are actually capable of?

00:12:59.413 --> 00:13:00.881 position:35% line:89% align:start
[cheering]

00:13:01.282 --> 00:13:02.483 position:38% line:83% align:start
[SUZURAN]
There you have it!

00:13:02.617 --> 00:13:05.019 position:24% line:83% align:start
I, Suzuran Kazami,
and my classmate,

00:13:05.152 --> 00:13:06.721 position:13% line:89% align:start
Ouka's ace, Sarasa Saionji,

00:13:06.854 --> 00:13:10.190 position:5% line:83% align:start
will be providin' live breakdown
and analysis fur ya!

00:13:10.324 --> 00:13:14.495 position:13% line:83% align:start
Okay, Urasaka, go on ahead
and name your game, right meow!

00:13:14.895 --> 00:13:17.498 position:38% line:83% align:start
[URASAKA]
Right. The game I choose is.

00:13:18.032 --> 00:13:20.502 position:24% line:83% align:start
The "anything goes"
one-hundred-meter race.

00:13:22.403 --> 00:13:23.705 position:27% line:89% align:start
Sturm und Drang!

00:13:23.837 --> 00:13:25.272 position:16% line:89% align:start
So, from start to finish,

00:13:25.406 --> 00:13:28.108 position:16% line:83% align:start
no mode of transportation
is off-limits, huh? Fun.

00:13:28.242 --> 00:13:29.977 position:21% line:83% align:start
I'm pretty confident
that you'll never beat me

00:13:30.110 --> 00:13:32.112 position:10% line:89% align:start
in a game of pure, raw speed.

00:13:32.246 --> 00:13:34.516 position:13% line:83% align:start
Well, that's a coincidence,
'cause I'm pretty confident

00:13:34.649 --> 00:13:36.518 position:21% line:83% align:start
you'll never beat me
in a game of anything.

00:13:36.651 --> 00:13:39.153 position:13% line:83% align:start
And it looks like the claws
are coming meowt!

00:13:39.286 --> 00:13:41.021 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
Man, what am I even saying

00:13:41.155 --> 00:13:42.289 position:30% line:89% align:start
