is context specific,

00:16:04.364 --> 00:16:05.900 position:19% line:89% align:start
so it rarely gets used,

00:16:06.033 --> 00:16:07.735 position:27% line:83% align:start
but it's perfect
against Nullify.

00:16:07.869 --> 00:16:10.304 position:30% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO] Okay,
but why use it for all three?

00:16:10.437 --> 00:16:12.039 position:35% line:83% align:start
[SHIRAYUKI]
At your true level, Master,

00:16:12.172 --> 00:16:14.642 position:13% line:83% align:start
one Level Three obstructive
ability will not be sufficient.

00:16:14.776 --> 00:16:18.145 position:19% line:83% align:start
Hence the redundancies.
The aggregation will compensate.

00:16:18.278 --> 00:16:19.848 position:30% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO] Yeah,
but what about the rest of it?

00:16:19.980 --> 00:16:22.416 position:13% line:83% align:start
Won't I need some abilities
on hand to balance out?

00:16:22.550 --> 00:16:25.185 position:35% line:83% align:start
-Oh, wait.
-[SHIRAYUKI] Now you get it.

00:16:25.687 --> 00:16:27.922 position:7% line:83% align:start
With the Company on your side,
you don't need to worry

00:16:28.055 --> 00:16:29.524 position:33% line:83% align:start
about things
like fair balancing.

00:16:29.657 --> 00:16:31.860 position:19% line:83% align:start
As long as our external
interference is unchecked,

00:16:31.992 --> 00:16:34.261 position:13% line:83% align:start
we can accomplish whatever
we need through hacking.

00:16:34.394 --> 00:16:35.630 position:19% line:89% align:start
So ultimately, Master,

00:16:35.763 --> 00:16:37.331 position:21% line:83% align:start
/the only real threat
you were facing

00:16:37.464 --> 00:16:39.233 position:13% line:89% align:start
/was Nullify Interference.

00:16:39.466 --> 00:16:42.937 position:10% line:83% align:start
The first ability I chose was
Completely Disable, Level Seven.

00:16:43.070 --> 00:16:45.305 position:24% line:83% align:start
That made sure that
my second ability, Force Stop,

00:16:45.439 --> 00:16:46.941 position:16% line:89% align:start
was entirely unhindered.

00:16:47.474 --> 00:16:49.309 position:30% line:83% align:start
But in reality,
it was Kagaya's hacking

00:16:49.443 --> 00:16:52.145 position:16% line:83% align:start
that made the bike stop,
after I restored her access.

00:16:52.279 --> 00:16:55.550 position:16% line:83% align:start
Oh, and for the last one,
my third choice,

00:16:55.683 --> 00:16:57.719 position:19% line:83% align:start
that we also activated
by hacking,

00:16:57.852 --> 00:17:00.722 position:24% line:83% align:start
was Safety Device,
that I used on you.

00:17:00.855 --> 00:17:04.091 position:13% line:83% align:start
I don't think I could sleep
at night if I got you hurt.

00:17:05.058 --> 00:17:05.860 position:38% line:89% align:start
[honking]

00:17:05.994 --> 00:17:07.227 position:35% line:89% align:start
[cheering]

00:17:07.361 --> 00:17:09.531 position:38% line:83% align:start
[SUZURAN]
The winner is Hiroto Shinohara!

00:17:09.664 --> 00:17:11.733 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
I can't believe that worked!

00:17:11.866 --> 00:17:13.300 position:19% line:89% align:start
The Company is amazing!

00:17:13.433 --> 00:17:15.770 position:5% line:89% align:start
Meow that's a Seven Star for ya!

00:17:16.236 --> 00:17:17.705 position:33% line:89% align:start
[chattering]

00:17:17.839 --> 00:17:19.507 position:35% line:89% align:start
[footsteps]

00:17:23.243 --> 00:17:24.979 position:10% line:83% align:start
While seeing you embarrassed
in public

00:17:25.112 --> 00:17:26.346 position:5% line:89% align:start
would bring me nothing but joy,

00:17:26.480 --> 00:17:28.115 position:27% line:83% align:start
I'm at least glad
you didn't lose to her.

00:17:28.248 --> 00:17:30.217 position:16% line:83% align:start
That honor's mine alone,
you hear?

00:17:30.652 --> 00:17:33.721 position:10% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO] Hey, are you trying
to tear off my tie, or my head?

00:17:33.855 --> 00:17:34.789 position:38% line:89% align:start
[scoffs]

00:17:36.089 --> 00:17:37.559 position:27% line:89% align:start
She's so violent.

00:17:40.862 --> 00:17:42.329 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
Hey, Miss Himeji?

00:17:42.462 --> 00:17:44.498 position:13% line:83% align:start
[SHIRAYUKI] There's no need
for the "Miss", Master.

00:17:44.632 --> 00:17:47.467 position:7% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO] My bad. Could you stop
listening in for a while?

00:17:47.602 --> 00:17:49.037 position:5% line:89% align:start
There's something I've gotta do,

00:17:49.169 --> 00:17:51.071 position:30% line:83% align:start
and I, uh kinda
wanna keep it private.

00:17:51.204 --> 00:17:53.340 position:16% line:89% align:start
I see. Is that an order?

00:17:53.808 --> 00:17:55.475 position:21% line:89% align:start
A request. So please.

00:17:55.610 --> 00:17:58.245 position:35% line:83% align:start
Very well,
if that's what you want, Master.

00:17:58.378 --> 00:17:59.781 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
It is, thank you.

00:18:00.113 --> 00:18:01.448 position:35% line:83% align:start
[SHIRAYUKI]
Right, but do you know

00:18:01.583 --> 00:18:03.216 position:38% line:83% align:start
I'm quite
the perceptive maid, Master.

00:18:03.350 --> 00:18:05.553 position:21% line:83% align:start
If you're to exploit
your popularity to pick up girls

00:18:05.687 --> 00:18:07.922 position:33% line:83% align:start
then I trust
you'll exercise discretion.

00:18:08.056 --> 00:18:09.591 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
Like I'd even do that!

00:18:09.724 --> 00:18:11.224 position:35% line:83% align:start
[SHIRAYUKI]
I'm kidding. Anyway.

00:18:11.358 --> 00:18:13.260 position:13% line:83% align:start
I'll disable the monitoring
for now.

00:18:13.761 --> 00:18:15.930 position:10% line:83% align:start
Please proceed with caution,
Master.

00:18:16.330 --> 00:18:19.099 position:35% line:83% align:start
-[stirring]
-[bell ringing]

00:18:19.232 --> 00:18:20.902 position:16% line:89% align:start
You're ridiculously late.

00:18:21.035 --> 00:18:22.704 position:21% line:83% align:start
Come on, do you know
how hard this place is

00:18:22.837 --> 00:18:25.506 position:21% line:83% align:start
to find for newbies?
It's like a gangster hideout.

00:18:25.640 --> 00:18:27.474 position:24% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO] Honestly,
it's a miracle I found it all.

00:18:27.609 --> 00:18:29.611 position:16% line:83% align:start
And I came straight away
like you asked, didn't I?

00:18:29.744 --> 00:18:32.647 position:16% line:83% align:start
[SARASA] Oh, it's excuse
after excuse with you, isn't it?

00:18:32.780 --> 00:18:35.683 position:7% line:83% align:start
Your mouth opens and out pours
an endless stream of nonsense.

00:18:35.817 --> 00:18:37.785 position:33% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO] Hey,
you have no business talking!

00:18:37.919 --> 00:18:40.420 position:13% line:83% align:start
What happened to that cute,
well-mannered princess I met?

00:18:40.555 --> 00:18:43.858 position:7% line:83% align:start
Uh? Cute? Well, I can't afford
to leave the real Sarasa

00:18:43.992 --> 00:18:46.027 position:7% line:83% align:start
a less-than-perfect reputation,
right?

00:18:46.561 --> 00:18:48.228 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
So, what's all this

00:18:48.362 --> 00:18:51.032 position:13% line:83% align:start
"Sarasa-body-double" stuff
about, anyway?

00:18:51.164 --> 00:18:53.166 position:38% line:83% align:start
[SARASA]
Alright. I'll tell you.

00:18:53.601 --> 00:18:55.302 position:5% line:89% align:start
But this stays between us, okay?

00:18:55.435 --> 00:18:57.005 position:21% line:83% align:start
Just like the secret
you told me.

00:18:57.137 --> 00:18:58.238 position:24% line:89% align:start
My lips are sealed.

00:18:58.539 --> 00:19:01.042 position:30% line:83% align:start
The real Sarasa
was actually kidnapped.

00:19:01.174 --> 00:19:02.342 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
Kidnapped?

00:19:03.578 --> 00:19:05.445 position:10% line:89% align:start
It was just over a year ago,

00:19:05.580 --> 00:19:07.715 position:16% line:83% align:start
shortly before I entered
Ouka Academy.

00:19:07.849 --> 00:19:10.652 position:16% line:83% align:start
But whoever kidnapped her
didn't issue any demands.

00:19:10.785 --> 00:19:12.720 position:21% line:83% align:start
[SARASA] I was a part
of Sarasa's friend group,

00:19:12.854 --> 00:19:15.355 position:13% line:83% align:start
so while her family waited
for leads on the kidnapper,

00:19:15.489 --> 00:19:17.091 position:7% line:89% align:start
I was asked to take her place.

00:19:17.224 --> 00:19:18.993 position:16% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO] What do you mean
when you say, "Friend group"?

00:19:19.127 --> 00:19:22.030 position:5% line:83% align:start
[SARASA] Children of the Saionji
family almost never go outside

00:19:22.162 --> 00:19:23.631 position:5% line:89% align:start
until they get into high school.

00:19:23.765 --> 00:19:26.067 position:19% line:83% align:start
Teachers and companions
are provided for them.

00:19:26.199 --> 00:19:27.535 position:35% line:89% align:start
Naturally,

00:19:27.669 --> 00:19:28.870 position:13% line:83% align:start
as a fantastically talented
and sweet girl,

00:19:29.003 --> 00:19:29.937 position:33% line:89% align:start
I was chosen.

00:19:30.071 --> 00:19:31.973 position:5% line:89% align:start
Better just let that one slide.

00:19:32.472 --> 00:19:34.776 position:35% line:83% align:start
Nobody knew
what her real face looked like.

00:19:34.909 --> 00:19:38.345 position:10% line:83% align:start
The Saionjis needed someone,
and I was happy to help them.

00:19:38.478 --> 00:19:40.882 position:33% line:83% align:start
I don't know
when she'll be returned to us,

00:19:41.015 --> 00:19:43.283 position:16% line:83% align:start
but until that day comes,
I have to protect

00:19:43.417 --> 00:19:45.720 position:27% line:83% align:start
Sarasa Saionji's
flawless reputation.

00:19:45.853 --> 00:19:48.422 position:16% line:83% align:start
I'm gonna need your help
with doing that, though.

00:19:48.556 --> 00:19:50.290 position:16% line:83% align:start
Because if words gets out
that I'm a fake,

00:19:50.424 --> 00:19:52.325 position:24% line:83% align:start
then what'll become
of the real Sarasa?

00:19:52.459 --> 00:19:53.695 position:33% line:89% align:start
The situation

00:19:53.828 --> 00:19:55.195 position:19% line:83% align:start
is significantly worse
than I thought.

00:19:55.328 --> 00:19:56.731 position:24% line:83% align:start
I can see the bind
that you're in.

00:19:56.864 --> 00:19:58.800 position:10% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO] You were able to lie
about who you were

00:19:58.933 --> 00:20:00.300 position:16% line:89% align:start
because of the Red Star.

00:20:00.434 --> 00:20:02.335 position:19% line:83% align:start
[SARASA] That's right,
and should you lose,

00:20:02.469 --> 00:20:03.604 position:24% line:89% align:start
my secret gets out.

00:20:03.738 --> 00:20:05.640 position:13% line:89% align:start
Whoever holds the Red Star,

00:20:05.773 --> 00:20:08.341 position:16% line:83% align:start
can see the entire record
of lies told with it.

00:20:08.743 --> 00:20:10.243 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
So then, if I ever lose,

00:20:10.377 --> 00:20:11.879 position:16% line:83% align:start
your lies will be exposed
as well as mine.

00:20:12.013 --> 00:20:14.048 position:19% line:83% align:start
[SARASA] If it gets out
that I'm not the true daughter

00:20:14.182 --> 00:20:15.783 position:19% line:89% align:start
of the Saionji family,

00:20:15.917 --> 00:20:18.586 position:7% line:83% align:start
then Eimei's Headmistress will
have no reason to protect you.

00:20:18.720 --> 00:20:22.222 position:5% line:83% align:start
She thinks you beat the Empress,
but I'm just Rina Akabane.

00:20:22.523 --> 00:20:25.526 position:21% line:83% align:start
And then, of course.
I'd have to leave the island.

00:20:25.660 --> 00:20:28.129 position:33% line:83% align:start
Hm? Why would
you be worried about leaving?

00:20:28.261 --> 00:20:29.831 position:13% line:89% align:start
Is staying that important?

00:20:29.964 --> 00:20:31.264 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
Yeah, it is.

00:20:31.398 --> 00:20:32.867 position:38% line:83% align:start
[SARASA]
Why?

00:20:33.000 --> 00:20:35.036 position:19% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO] Well, you see.
There's someone I'm looking for.

00:20:35.169 --> 00:20:37.672 position:13% line:83% align:start
A childhood friend of mine
I haven't seen in years,

00:20:37.805 --> 00:20:40.007 position:33% line:83% align:start
but I'm sure
she's here on the island.

00:20:40.141 --> 00:20:41.843 position:16% line:89% align:start
And so, until I find her,

00:20:41.976 --> 00:20:44.645 position:24% line:83% align:start
getting kicked out
is just not an option for me.

00:20:45.747 --> 00:20:47.115 position:38% line:83% align:start
[SARASA]
That means...

00:20:47.247 --> 00:20:49.217 position:19% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO] My only option
is to maintain the lie

00:20:49.349 --> 00:20:51.152 position:5% line:89% align:start
that I'm the strongest there is.

00:20:51.284 --> 00:20:52.920 position:38% line:83% align:start
[SARASA]
You know, I hate to admit it,

00:20:53.054 --> 00:20:55.056 position:5% line:89% align:start
but as long you continue to win.

00:20:55.189 --> 00:20:57.925 position:10% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO] My lie and your lie
will be protected.

00:20:58.391 --> 00:21:00.427 position:5% line:89% align:start
Guess we've formed an alliance.

00:21:01.095 --> 00:21:02.530 position:41% line:89% align:start
[sighs]

00:21:02.663 --> 00:21:04.766 position:21% line:83% align:start
Shall we exchange IDs
so we can stay in contact, then?

00:21:04.899 --> 00:21:08.401 position:19% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO] Yeah, I guess.
Wait. My name's top trending?

00:21:08.536 --> 00:21:09.804 position:38% line:83% align:start
[SARASA]
What are you talking about?

00:21:09.937 --> 00:21:11.572 position:24% line:83% align:start
It's been like that
since you got here.

00:21:11.706 --> 00:21:13.440 position:38% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO]
Ew, what's with this guy?

00:21:13.574 --> 00:21:14.876 position:21% line:89% align:start
It's all "my goddess"

00:21:15.009 --> 00:21:16.644 position:7% line:83% align:start
and "she isn't made for losing"
and stuff.

00:21:16.778 --> 00:21:18.880 position:5% line:89% align:start
Are all your fans this zealous?

00:21:19.013 --> 00:21:21.182 position:13% line:83% align:start
I attract a whole spectrum
of them,

00:21:21.314 --> 00:21:22.884 position:38% line:83% align:start
but when
you're as talented as I am,

00:21:23.017 --> 00:21:25.153 position:21% line:83% align:start
some people are bound
to be mesmerized.

00:21:25.285 --> 00:21:27.054 position:5% line:89% align:start
I'm calling you out on that one.

00:21:27.955 --> 00:21:31.458 position:19% line:83% align:start
Look, it might be best
if we act friendly.

00:21:31.893 --> 00:21:35.029 position:19% line:83% align:start
[HIROTO] You're right.
I mean, after all, we're allies.

00:21:39.233 --> 00:21:40.367 position:33% line:89% align:start
[door opens]

00:21:40.500 --> 00:21:41.736 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:21:42.402 --> 00:21:44.471 position:21% line:83% align:start
Good evening, Master,
welcome home.

00:21:44.605 --> 00:21:46.439 position:13% line:89% align:start
Sorry to keep you waiting.

00:21:48.709 --> 00:21:49.610 position:47% line:89% align:start
Oh?

00:21:50.410 --> 00:21:52.713 position:5% line:89% align:start
Ah-ha! So he's alive after all.

00:21:52.847 --> 00:21:54.882 position:5% line:83% align:start
[SARASA] Why the heck didn't you
send me a text last night,

00:21:55.016 --> 00:21:56.284 position:24% line:89% align:start
you arrogant jerk?

00:21:56.416 --> 00:21:59.253 position:30% line:83% align:start
Sorry, my bad.
Busy schedule, you know?

00:21:59.419 --> 00:22:00.955 position:10% line:89% align:start
Life of a Seven Star and all.

00:22:01.088 --> 00:22:03.356 position:33% line:83% align:start
That's a lie.
I was totally passed out.

00:22:03.490 --> 00:22:05.059 position:21% line:89% align:start
Oh, stop showing off.

00:22:05.193 --> 00:22:08.196 position:13% line:83% align:start
I just swung by to show you
that you hadn't broken me yet.

00:22:08.328 --> 00:22:09.764 position:41% line:89% align:start
Humph!

00:22:09.897 --> 00:22:11.498 position:38% line:89% align:start
[laughs]

00:22:11.632 --> 00:22:13.601 position:21% line:89% align:start
Who the heck is that?

00:22:13.734 --> 00:22:16.571 position:38% line:89% align:start
[laughs]

